The paper discusses false data injection attacks on smart grids, which is a topic related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and control systems (cs.SY). The proposed technique involves sparse optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions experimental evaluation on IEEE benchmark test systems, which suggests a focus on networking and internet technologies (cs.NI).
